Package com.intellij.openapi.editor.markup

Class GutterIconRenderer

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.intellij.openapi.editor.markup.GutterIconRenderer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    GutterMark, PossiblyDumbAware, SimpleAccessible
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BoundIconRenderer, DiffGutterRenderer, GutterActionRenderer, LineMarkerInfo.LineMarkerGutterIconRenderer, NavigationGutterIconRenderer, XBreakpointBase.BreakpointGutterIconRenderer

    public abstract class GutterIconRenderer
extends java.lang.Object
implements GutterMark, PossiblyDumbAware, SimpleAccessible
    Interface which should be implemented in order to draw icons in the gutter area and handle events for them. Gutter icons are drawn to the left of the folding area and can be used, for example, to mark implemented or overridden methods.

    Daemon code analyzer checks newly arrived gutter icon renderer against the old one and if they are equal, does not redraw the icon. So it is highly advisable to override hashCode()/equals() methods to avoid icon flickering when old gutter renderer gets replaced with the new. Proper implementation of equals is also important for instances used to specify gutter icons for inlays (see EditorCustomElementRenderer.calcGutterIconRenderer(Inlay))

    During indexing, methods are only invoked for renderers implementing DumbAware.

    See Also:
    RangeHighlighter.setGutterIconRenderer(GutterIconRenderer), Inlay.getGutterIconRenderer(), EditorCustomElementRenderer.calcGutterIconRenderer(Inlay)
